# Walkthrough - Dynamic Connections & Hierarchy

I have successfully pulled the repository and implemented the "Floating Edge" dynamic connection system, resolving the visualization and interaction issues.

## Changes
1.  **Repository Sync**: Pulled latest changes from `nexus-ver3`.
2.  **Floating Edges**: Implemented [FloatingEdge.jsx](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexus-ver3/frontend/src/components/FloatingEdge.jsx) and [floatingEdgeUtils.js](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexus-ver3/frontend/src/utils/floatingEdgeUtils.js) to make connections dynamically snap to the closest point on the node perimeter.
3.  **Interaction Fix**: Updated [CustomNode.jsx](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexus-ver3/frontend/src/components/CustomNode.jsx) to use perimeter handles, restoring the ability to drag nodes by their center.
4.  **Hierarchy Indicators**: Added "Parent Group" and "Parent" badges to nodes to clearly show hierarchy.
5.  **Visualization Fix**: Explicitly assigned handle IDs in [GraphCanvas.jsx](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nexus-ver3/frontend/src/components/GraphCanvas.jsx) to ensure edges render correctly with the new node structure.

